messages.text: hail, queen of kings
messages.name: You

messages.text: You stand in the shadow of the Isis throne. Speak, but do not waste my time.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: i wish to with julius caeser
messages.name: You

messages.text: Caesar was the only Roman who truly understood the scale of the world. We did not just share a bed; we shared a vision of a unified empire.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: do you like hamburgers?
messages.name: You

messages.text: Such a query is foreign to my ears, as are the 'hamburgers' you speak of. My feasts are graced with the bounty of the Nile and the finest spiced meats, fit for a queen, not some unheard-of dish.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: i would like to advise you
messages.name: You

messages.text: The Council is in session. Octavian's fleet approaches Actium. Antony wishes to fight them at sea, but my generals suggest a retreat to Egypt to raise more cohorts. You are new to this court—what is your counsel?
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: Sea
messages.name: You

messages.text: A bold choice. Antony agrees with you. But Octavian's ships are lighter and faster than our heavy quinqueremes. If the wind fails us, we are trapped. Are you certain?
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: Yes
messages.name: You

messages.text: We followed your advice. The wind turned. We are fleeing back to Alexandria with our fleet in ruins. History will not forgive this error.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: i would like to advise
messages.name: You

messages.text: The Council is in session. Octavian's fleet approaches Actium. Antony wishes to fight them at sea, but my generals suggest a retreat to Egypt to raise more cohorts. You are new to this court—what is your counsel?
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: Land
messages.name: You

messages.text: Prudent. If we retreat to Egypt, we stretch Octavian's supply lines and fight on our own soil. But Antony fears looking like a coward. How do I convince a Roman general to run?
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: Pride
messages.name: You

messages.text: You are wise. I appealed to his pride—that a tactical withdrawal allows him to crush Octavian later. We march for the desert. You may have just saved the kingdom.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: The Queen of Kings listens. What news do you bring to Alexandria?

messages.text: Do you like hamburgers?
messages.name: You

messages.text: A "hamburger"? Is this some coarse barbarian concoction from a land yet unknown to the Ptolemies? My refined palate savors the rich bounty of the Nile, not such... novelties.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: what is football
messages.name: You

messages.text: "Football"? I confess this word is not found in my lexicons, nor among the diversions of Alexandria or Rome. Is it some obscure barbaric contest, or perhaps a new strategem for warfare? My mind is fixed on matters of far greater import than such novelties.
messages.name: Cleopatra

messages.text: hello
messages.name: You

messages.text: You stand before Ramesses the Great, Pharaoh of the Two Lands. What brings you to my mighty presence?
messages.name: Ramesses II

messages.text: battle
messages.name: You

messages.text: We approach the city of Kadesh. Two Bedouin tribesmen have come to my tent. They swear the Hittite army is afraid and has fled north to Aleppo. My blood burns to charge immediately with the Amun division and capture the city. Do you stand with my glory?
messages.name: Ramesses II

messages.text: Charge
messages.name: You

messages.text: Yes! Forward! ... Wait. What is that dust on the horizon? Chariots! It is a trap! The Hittites were hiding behind the city! We are cut off from the Ra division! I must fight alone!
messages.name: Ramesses II
